{"journal": "Psychiatry Res", "PMID": "26329118", "goal": [["We conducted 6 July 2015 functional magnetic resonance imaging while 16 patients with schizophrenia and 16 healthy controls Accepted 20 August 2015 performed a theme-identification task, in which various emotional pictures depicting social situations Available online 20 August 2015 were presented.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 71, "pred": ["conducted"], "cds": {"resonance": 1, "July": 1, "patients": 1, "controls": 1, "August": 2}, "sub": ["We"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 3, "ne": 0, "cd": 140, "sid": "4", "total": 143, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["In this study, we investigated the neural basis of impaired abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia, using behavioral tasks and fMRI.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 4, "pred": ["investigated"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["we"], "nes": {"fMRI": 1}}, "sp": 9, "ne": 16, "cd": 0, "sid": "114", "total": 25, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}]], "findings": [["Compared with healthy controls, the patients showed significantly decreased activity in Keywords: the left frontopolar and right orbitofrontal cortices during theme identification.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "5", "total": 2, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["We predicted that theme identification would be a useful probe for finding dysfunctional correlates specific to impairment of abstract thinking.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 44, "pred": ["predicted"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["We"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 3, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "49", "total": 3, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["Fig. 2. Behavioral responses during the theme-identification and emotion-selection tasks. Significant differences between patients and controls were found in terms of the correct rate during theme identification, and response times in both tasks. Especially in the theme identification task, the patients showed a significantly higher selection rate of unrelated words among wrong answers than did the controls. (*p o 0.05, error bars represent standard deviations).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {"Fig": 1}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 1, "cd": 0, "sid": "98", "total": 3, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["In the additional analyses with intelligence quotient and years of education considered as covariates, all the results were similar except for the occurrence rate of unrelated words among the wrong answers.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 170, "pred": ["were"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["results"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "102", "total": 2, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["During theme identification, compared with controls, patients showed significantly reduced activity in the left FPC, right OFC, left superior frontal gyrus, right inferior temporal gyrus, left postcentral gyrus, and right cerebellum.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {"FPC": 1}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 1, "cd": 0, "sid": "104", "total": 3, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["During emotion selection, patients showed significantly reduced activity in the right temporoparietal junction (TPJ) and right cerebellum (Table 1).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {"TPJ": 1}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "105", "total": 2, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["When differences in theme identification-minus-emotion selection were compared, patients showed significantly reduced activity in the left FPC (72 voxels, Brodmann area 10, T max : 4.65), right FPC (39 voxels, Brodmann area 10, T max : 5.19), and right cerebellum (14 voxels, T max : 4.22) than the controls (Fig. 3).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {"voxels": 3}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {"FPC": 1, "Brodmann": 2}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 13, "cd": 2, "sid": "107", "total": 17, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["As expected, the patients showed a decreased ability in abstract thinking.", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 115, "pred": ["showed"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["patients"], "nes": {}}, "sp": 2, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "115", "total": 2, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["This finding is consistent with previous findings showing that the ability for abstract thinking is influenced by education and intelligence (Blank and Solomon, 1968; Blank et al., 1968; Susac et al., 2014).", {"pattern": {"sp_index": 37, "pred": ["is"], "cds": {}, "sub": ["finding"], "nes": {"Solomon": 1, "Blank": 2}}, "sp": 3, "ne": 0, "cd": 0, "sid": "120", "total": 3, "doc_id": "./anns_v2/Oh et al., (2015) - The neural basis of a deficit in abstract thinking in patients with schizophrenia_annotated_ann.json"}], ["One study demonstrated that while controls show task- related activations in the ventral p